# Project: {{TITLE}} (RAG Library)

## Intent

Build a semantic search + RAG chat library for {{AUTHOR}}'s corpus.
Forked from the alan-watts RAG scaffold ‚Äî a proven stack of FastAPI,
pgvector, and Next.js, now configured for {{AUTHOR}}'s content.

**Goal**: Index {{AUTHOR}}'s lectures/essays/writings and build a chat interface
where users can talk to an AI embodying {{AUTHOR}}, grounded in actual transcript excerpts.

## Stack

- Backend: FastAPI (Python 3.11) @ port {{API_PORT}}
- Database: PostgreSQL 16 + pgvector @ port {{DB_PORT}}
- Embeddings: all-mpnet-base-v2 (local, 768d)
- Frontend: Next.js 14 (TypeScript + Tailwind) @ port {{FE_PORT}}
- Config: config/library.yml (single source of identity)
- LLM: Pluggable (Anthropic | OpenAI | Ollama | Gemini | OpenRouter)
- Fork: Scaffolded from alan-watts via scripts/fork-library.sh

## Constraints

- Zero breaking changes to scaffold behavior
- DB binds to 127.0.0.1 only ‚Äî never 0.0.0.0
- Re-embedding is expensive ‚Äî never auto-trigger embed.py
- Secrets in ~/.secrets/hercules.env, never committed to git
- NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL must be baked in at Docker build time

## Architecture

```
Query ‚Üí Embed (all-mpnet-base-v2, 768d, local)
  ‚Üí pgvector HNSW cosine search ‚Üí Top-k chunks + parent transcripts
  ‚Üí RAG prompt (built from config/library.yml ragPersona)
  ‚Üí LLM (pluggable)
  ‚Üí Response grounded in actual transcripts
```

Library identity: `config/library.yml` ‚Üí `config/library_config.py` ‚Üí `config/settings.py` ‚Üí all modules

